Package: valr
Type: Package
Title: Genome interval arithmetic in R
Version: 0.1
Authors@R: as.person(c(
    "Jay Hesselberth <jay.hesselberth@gmail.com> [aut, cre]",
    "Kent Riemondy <kent.riemondy@ucdenver.edu> [aut]",
    "Ryan Sheridan <ryan.sheridan@ucdenver.edu> [ctb]"
  ))
Description: Read and manipulate genome intervals and signals. valr 
             provides functionality similar to BEDtools and bedops within R,
             enabling interactive analysis and visualization of genome-scale data. 
License: MIT + file LICENSE
Depends:
    R (>= 3.1.2)
Imports:
    dplyr (>= 0.5.0),
    lazyeval,
    purrr,
    readr,
    Rcpp (>= 0.12.3),
    stringr,
    tibble,
    tidyr,
    broom,
SystemRequirements: C++11
LinkingTo: Rcpp (>= 0.12.3), BH, dplyr (>= 0.5.0)
Suggests:
    knitr,
    rmarkdown,
    testthat,
    microbenchmark,
    covr,
    ggplot2,
    shinydashboard
VignetteBuilder: knitr
RoxygenNote: 5.0.1
